# BROWSER-notifications.md - LinkedIn Notification, Reply & Connection Patterns

## SS 1. Extract Notifications

```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 3000)); var notifications = document.querySelectorAll('[data-finite-scroll-hotkey-item]'); return Array.from(notifications).slice(0, 15).map(function(notif) { var card = notif.querySelector('.nt-card'); var text = notif.innerText; var links = Array.from(notif.querySelectorAll('a')); var isReply = text.includes('commented on') || text.includes('replied to') || text.includes('mentioned you in a comment'); var isLike = text.includes('reacted to') || text.includes('liked'); var profileLink = links.find(function(a) { return a.href.includes('/in/'); }); var activityLink = links.find(function(a) { return a.href.includes('/feed/update/') || a.href.includes('/activity/'); }); var username = profileLink ? decodeURIComponent(profileLink.href.split('/in/')[1].split('/')[0].split('?')[0]) : null; var fullUrl = activityLink ? activityLink.href : null; var baseUrl = fullUrl ? fullUrl.split('?')[0] : null; return { type: isReply ? 'reply' : (isLike ? 'like' : 'other'), username: username, postUrl: fullUrl, baseUrl: baseUrl, preview: text.slice(0, 200), unread: card ? card.classList.contains('nt-card--unread') : false }; }).filter(function(n) { return n.type === 'reply' && n.postUrl && n.username; }); }"}
ENDJSON
```

## SS 5. Reply to Comment (Post Detail Page)

Post pages have multiple TipTap editors. For notification replies, click Reply on the target comment first to open the correct threaded editor.

### Step 0: Click Reply on the target comment

Replace `${notificationAuthor}` with the commenter's name, `${notificationPreviewSnippet}` with a unique snippet from their comment.

```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 3000)); var comments = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('article[class*=\"comment\"]')); var targetComment = comments.find(function(c) { return c.innerText.trim().startsWith(window.__data.author) && c.innerText.includes(window.__data.snippet); }); if (!targetComment) { targetComment = comments.find(function(c) { return c.innerText.trim().startsWith(window.__data.author) && c.innerText.includes('{{name}}'); }); } if (!targetComment) return { error: 'target comment not found', commentCount: comments.length }; var btns = Array.from(targetComment.querySelectorAll('button')); var replyBtn = btns.find(function(b) { return b.innerText.trim() === 'Reply'; }); if (!replyBtn) return { error: 'no Reply button on target comment' }; replyBtn.click(); await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 2000)); var editorInside = targetComment.querySelector('[contenteditable=\"true\"][role=\"textbox\"]'); return { clicked: true, editorOpen: !!editorInside }; }", "data": {"author": "Author Name", "snippet": "unique snippet from their comment"}}
ENDJSON
```

If `editorOpen: false` → retry once. Still fails → skip, log error.

### Step 1: Type text in the THREADED reply editor

LinkedIn auto-inserts `@AuthorName` when Reply is clicked. Find the editor containing this @mention — that's the correct threaded editor.
Pass `author` (notification author name) and `text` (reply) in the `data` field.

```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 1000)); var editors = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('[contenteditable=\"true\"][role=\"textbox\"]')); var replyBox = editors.find(function(e) { return e.textContent.includes(window.__data.author); }); if (!replyBox) return { success: false, reason: 'no-editor-with-mention' }; replyBox.focus(); await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 300)); document.execCommand('insertText', false, window.__data.text); await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 500)); return { success: true, typed: replyBox.textContent.slice(0, 80) }; }", "data": {"author": "Author Name", "text": "YOUR_REPLY_HERE"}}
ENDJSON
```

### Step 2: Submit + verify

Replace `${expectedSnippet}` with a short unique fragment from your reply text.

```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { var btns = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('button')).filter(function(b) { return (b.innerText.trim() === 'Reply' || b.innerText.trim() === 'Comment') && b.offsetParent !== null && b.getBoundingClientRect().width > 0; }); var btn = btns[btns.length - 1]; if (!btn) return { success: false, reason: 'no-submit-button' }; if (btn.disabled) return { success: false, reason: 'button-disabled' }; btn.click(); await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 3000)); var posted = document.body.innerText.includes(window.__data.snippet); return { submitted: true, posted: posted }; }", "data": {"snippet": "unique snippet from your reply"}}
ENDJSON
```

If NOT posted: retry ONCE. Still fails → skip, retry next heartbeat.

### When to use SS 5 vs top-level comment:
- **Notification replies** (§ 3 in HEARTBEAT.md): Step 0 → Step 1 → Step 2 (threaded reply)
- **Proactive comments** (§ 4 browse_and_engage): Use BROWSER-engage.md SS 4 (no Step 0)

## SS 7. Send Connection Request (with personalized note)

### Step 1: Safety checks (on profile page)

```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 3000)); var vanity = window.location.pathname.replace('/in/', '').replace(/\\/$/, ''); var els = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('button, a')).filter(e => e.offsetParent !== null && e.getBoundingClientRect().y < 600); var hasFollow = els.some(e => (e.getAttribute('aria-label') || '').startsWith('Follow ' + vanity.replace(/-/g, ' ').split(' ')[0])); if (!hasFollow) hasFollow = els.some(e => e.innerText.trim() === 'Follow' && (e.getAttribute('aria-label') || '').startsWith('Follow')); var hasPending = els.some(e => e.innerText.trim() === 'Pending'); if (!hasFollow && !hasPending) return { canConnect: false, skipReason: 'already-connected', vanityName: vanity }; if (hasPending) return { canConnect: false, skipReason: 'already-pending', vanityName: vanity }; var bodyText = document.body.innerText.slice(0, 1500); var lines = bodyText.split(String.fromCharCode(10)); var headline = ''; for (var i = 0; i < lines.length; i++) { if (lines[i].trim() === 'Follow' || lines[i].trim() === 'More') { for (var j = i - 1; j >= 0; j--) { if (lines[j].trim().length > 0) { headline = lines[j].trim(); break; } } break; } } var recruiterKeywords = ['Recruiter', 'Recruiting', 'Talent Acquisition', 'Hiring Manager', 'HR', 'Headhunter']; for (var k = 0; k < recruiterKeywords.length; k++) { if (headline.includes(recruiterKeywords[k])) return { canConnect: false, headline: headline.slice(0, 150), skipReason: 'recruiter-headline', vanityName: vanity }; } return { canConnect: true, headline: headline.slice(0, 150), vanityName: vanity }; }"}
ENDJSON
```

If `canConnect: false` → log skip reason, continue.

### Step 2: Navigate to custom-invite URL

Replace `${vanityName}` with the profile vanity name from Step 1.
```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/navigate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{"url":"https://www.linkedin.com/preload/custom-invite/?vanityName=${vanityName}"}' 2>&1
```

### Step 3: Click "Add a note", type note, click Send

Pass connection note text in the `data` field (max 300 chars).

```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 3000)); var btns = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('button')); var addNoteBtn = btns.find(function(b) { return b.innerText.trim() === 'Add a note' && b.offsetParent !== null; }); if (!addNoteBtn) return { sent: false, error: 'no Add a note button' }; addNoteBtn.click(); await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 1500)); var textarea = document.querySelector('textarea#custom-message'); if (!textarea) return { sent: false, error: 'no note textarea' }; var nativeInputValueSetter = Object.getOwnPropertyDescriptor(window.HTMLTextAreaElement.prototype, 'value').set; nativeInputValueSetter.call(textarea, window.__data.text); textarea.dispatchEvent(new Event('input', { bubbles: true })); textarea.dispatchEvent(new Event('change', { bubbles: true })); await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 1000)); btns = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('button')); var sendBtn = btns.find(function(b) { return b.innerText.trim() === 'Send' && b.offsetParent !== null; }); if (!sendBtn) return { sent: false, typed: true, error: 'no Send button' }; sendBtn.click(); await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 2000)); return { sent: true }; }", "data": {"text": "YOUR_CONNECTION_NOTE"}}
ENDJSON
```

### Connection Note Rules

- Max 300 characters
- Personalize: reference their headline, role, or a post they wrote
- Keep casual, genuine
- Template: "hey {firstName}, {specific thing you noticed about them}. {brief connection to your work}. would be great to connect"

If `sent: true` → log, update `weekly.connection_requests`. Navigate back to notifications.
